# General
Peter ..Godfrey-Smith, ``Theory and Reality: An Introduction to the Philosophy of Science'', Chicago: Chicago University Press, 2003, available from the ..Co-Op book shop. _This is a very good book to use if you don't like the Ladyman book for any reason._

Simon Blackburn, ``Oxford Dictionary of Philosophy'', any edition, Oxford: Oxford University Press, available from the ..Co-Op book shop or second-hand bookshops

Stathis Psillos, ``Philosophy of Science A-Z'', Edinburgh: Edinburgh University Press, 2007, available from the ..Co-Op book shop: ..$29.95

The Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy (entirely online): http://setis.library.usyd.edu.au/stanford/contents.html

(The Philosophy of Science by Stephen Toulmin is a good read. Published by Hutchinson University Library) *fawn Thanks. And put your name, please. Recommending things here is worth marks too, not just what you write on the discussion pages. Jason*

This book: (Curd & Cover, _Philosophy of Science: The Central Issues_) [added by Hugh.Parsonage] http://www.amazon.com/Philosophy-Science-Central-J-Cover/dp/0393971759/ref=pd_bbs_sr_1?ie=UTF8&s=books&qid=1207546922&sr=8-1

# Before lecture 3, March the 4th:
- ftp://xeny.net/Grossman-EBM-preprint.pdf

# Before lecture 6, March the 12th:
- ``Einstein and the Quantum Spooks'' by Huw Price, available at http://www.usyd.edu.au/time/price/preprints/Price_ISS05c.pdf

For those interested in the Kuhn v. Popper debate, the following may be of interest:
Fuller, Steve (2003). _Kuhn vs. Popper: The Struggle for the Soul of Science._ Cambridge: Icon Books.

Dick Parker

